Arcane Schooling		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Arcane Schooling]								PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Deep Imaskari],[PREREGION:Underdark (Deep Imaskar)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Chessenta],[PREREGION:Golden Water],[PREREGION:Halruaa],[PREREGION:Lantan],[PREREGION:Mulhorand],[PREREGION:Nimbral],[PREREGION:Unther],[PREREGION:Wizards' Reach]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Planetouched],[PREREGION:Chessenta]]																																																									DESC:In your homeland, all who show some skill at the Art may receive training as arcane spellcasters. Thus, many characters know something of the ways of the bard, the sorcerer, or the wizard.					STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:TEMPLATE|Bard Favored Class|Sorcerer Favored Class|Wizard Favored Class	SELECT:1																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.33		DESC:Choose one arcane spellcasting class (bard, sorcerer, or wizard). You can activate spell trigger magic items as if you had 1 level in the selected class. The selected class also becomes a favored class for you in addition to any other favored class you have or select. For example, a multiclass human fighter/rogue who selects wizard for this feat could add levels of wizard without taking any experience penalty for multiclassing in three classes. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat. If you are a specialist wizard and you choose either sorcerer or wizard as the selected class for this feat, you may activate spell-trigger items from your opposing schools.
Artist			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Artist]						PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Elf],[PREREGION:Sildeyuir],[PREREGION:Snow Eagle Aerie]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Gnome],[PREREGION:Thesk],[PREREGION:Western Heartlands]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Half-Elf],[PREREGION:Dalelands]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Chessenta],[PREREGION:Waterdeep],[PREREGION:Western Heartlands]]																																																												DESC:Your people are renowned for their skill at story and song.																											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SKILL|Craft (Calligraphy)|Craft (Painting)|Craft (Sculpting)|Craft (Weaving)	SELECT:1																																																																																																					BONUS:VAR|BardicMusicTimes|3			BONUS:SKILL|TYPE=Perform,%LIST|2																											SOURCEPAGE:p.33		DESC:You gain a +2 bonus on all Perform checks and on checks with one Craft skill that involves art, such as calligraphy, painting, sculpture, or weaving. In addition, if you have the bardic music ability, you may use it three additional times per day. For example, a 3rd-level bard with this feat could use her bardic music ability six times per day. Normal: A bard can use her bardic music ability once per day per bard level. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Axethrower			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Axethrower]							PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Dwarf],[PREREGION:Great Glacier]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Great Glacier],[PREREGION:Moonshae Isles],[PREREGION:North],[PREREGION:Vaasa]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Lizardfolk],[PREREGION:Surkh]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc],[PREREGION:Moonsea],[PREREGION:Underdark (Northdark]]																																																												DESC:You have learned how to hurl heavy weapons to deadly effect.																																																																																																																																								BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.THROWN|max(STR,DEX)-DEX																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.33		DESC:When you make a ranged attack with a thrown weapon (axe, spear, javelin, or the like), you may add your Strength bonus instead of your Dexterity bonus to the attack roll. Normal: A character attacking with a ranged weapon adds his Dexterity bonus to the attack roll. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Blooded			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Blooded]						PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Centaur,Gnoll],[PREREGION:Plateau of Thay]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Dwarf],[PREREGION:Underdark (Earthroot)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Elf],[PREREGION:Cormanthor Drow],[PREREGION:Inner Sea],[PREREGION:Underdark (Menzoberranyr)],[PREREGION:Outer Sea]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Grimlock],[PREREGION:Underdark (Reeshov)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Halfling],[PREREGION:Chondalwood]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Dalelands],[PREREGION:Nelanther Isles],[PREREGION:Silverymoon],[PREREGION:Tethyr]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc],[PREREGION:Underdark (Northdark)],[PREREGION:Vaasa]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Planetouched],[PREREGION:Delimbiyr Vale]]		DESC:You know what it means to fight for your life, and you understand the value of quick wits and quicker reactions when blades are bared and deadly spells are chanted.																																										ASPECT:Immunity|Shaken Condition																																																																							BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2														BONUS:SKILL|Spot|2																													SOURCEPAGE:p.35		DESC:You get a +2 bonus on initiative checks and a +2 bonus on Spot checks. You cannot become shaken, and you ignore the effects of the shaken condition. However, you can still be frightened or panicked. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
