Horse Nomad			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Horse Nomad]						PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Hordelands],[PREREGION:Ride],[PREREGION:Shaar]]																																																																																																		DESC:You have been raised in a culture that relies upon riding and shooting.																																																			AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Shortbow|Lance|Scimitar																																																																																															BONUS:SKILL|Ride|3																													SOURCEPAGE:p.39		DESC:You gain proficiency with the composite shortbow, lance, and scimitar. You also get a +3 bonus on all Ride checks. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Knifefighter		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Knifefighter]					PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Bugbear,Goblin,Hobgoblin],[PREREGION:Earthfast Mountains]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Chitine],[PREREGION:Underdark (Yathchol)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Half-Elf],[PREREGION:Dambrath],[PREREGION:Dragon Coast]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Halfling],[PREREGION:Channath Vale]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Anauroch],[PREREGION:Dambrath],[PREREGION:Lake of Steam],[PREREGION:Sword Coast]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc],[PREREGION:Thesk]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Planetouched],[PREREGION:Chessenta]]																										DESC:You're an expert at using weapons in a grapple.																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.40		DESC:You can use a light weapon to attack your opponent in a grapple with no penalty on the attack roll. In addition, you need not win a grapple check to draw a light weapon while grappling, although you still must use a move action to do so. If your base attack bonus is +6 or higher, you can make a full attack with a light weapon while grappling, provided that you already have your weapon drawn. Normal: A character in a grapple takes a -4 penalty on attack rolls when attacking the grappled opponent with a light weapon. A character in a grapple must win a grapple check in order to draw a weapon and cannot make a full attack in the round she does so. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Luck of Heroes		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Luck of Heroes]						PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Elf],[PREREGION:Elven Court],[PREREGION:Forest of Lethyr],[PREREGION:Yuirwood]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Gloaming],[PREREGION:Sphur Upra]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Half-Elf],[PREREGION:Aglarond]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Halfling],[PREREGION:Channath Vale],[PREREGION:Western Heartlands]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Aglarond],[PREREGION:Dalelands],[PREREGION:Tethyr],[PREREGION:Turmish],[PREREGION:Vast]]																																									DESC:Your land is known for producing heroes. Through pluck, determination, and resilience, you survive when no one expects you to come through.																																																																								BONUS:SAVE|ALL|1|TYPE=Luck																																														BONUS:COMBAT|AC|1|TYPE=Luck																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.40		DESC:You receive a +1 luck bonus on all saving throws and a +1 luck bonus to Armor Class. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Magic in the Blood	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Magic in the Blood]					PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Dwarf],[PREREGION:Oldonnar],[PREREGION:Underdark (Darklands)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Elf],[PREREGION:Underdark (Menzoberranyr)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Gnome],[PREREGION:Great Dale],[PREREGION:Thesk],[PREREGION:Underdark (Northdark)]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Kir-lanan],[PREREGION:Far Hills]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Planetouched],[PREREGION:Calimshan],[PREREGION:Delimbiyr Vale],[PREREGION:Mulhorand],[PREREGION:Unther]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Spirit Folk],[PREREGION:Ashane]]																															DESC:You have a knack for getting the most out of your innate magical abilities. You can use them more often than others of your race can.																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|RacialSpellTimes|2																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.40		DESC:You can use your racial spell-like abilities more often than you otherwise could. Any ability that is otherwise usable once per day is now usable three times per day. Special: You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
Magical Training		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Regional.LevelOneFeatOnly	VISIBLE:EXPORT									PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Regional],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Magical Training]	PRESTAT:1,INT=10,CHA=10		PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Elf],[PREREGION:Evereska],[PREREGION:Evermeet]],[PREMULT:2,[PRERACE:1,Human],[PREREGION:Halruaa],[PREREGION:Nimbral]]																																																																																										DESC:You come from a land where cantrips are taught to all who have the aptitude to learn magic. Every crafter and artisan, it seems, knows a minor spell or two.																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Magical Training|3										SOURCEPAGE:p.41		DESC:You can cast three 0-level arcane spells per day as either a sorcerer or wizard (your choice, so long as you have a score of at least 10 in the ability that controls the spellcasting for that class). You must make this decision when you first take the feat. Thereafter, you have an arcane spell failure chance if you wear armor and are treated as a sorcerer or wizard of your arcane spellcaster level (minimum 1st) for the purpose of determining level-based variables of the spells you cast. If you choose to cast spells as a sorcerer, the DC for saves against your spells is 10 + your Cha modifier. You know two 0-level spells of your choice from the sorcerer/wizard list. If you choose to cast spells as a wizard, the DC for saves against your spells is 10 + your Int modifier. You have a spellbook with three 0-level spells of your choice from the sorcerer/ wizard list. You prepare your spells exactly as a wizard does. Special: If you already have levels in sorcerer or wizard, increase the number of 0-level spells you can cast per day by three. You may select this feat only as a 1st-level character. You may have only one regional feat.
