Gift of Discernment		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Exalted	PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG																						PRETEXT:Assigned by DM							DESC:You can rely on your conscience to steer you away from evil deeds.																																																																								COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:If you take a moment (a free action) to contemplate an action you are about to perform, you know with certainty whether that action will adversely affect your alignment and standing with your deity (if any). This knowledge is identical with that provided by a phylactery of faithfulness.
Lliira's Blessing			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Exalted	PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG								PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Nimbus of Light	PRESKILL:1,Escape Artist=1					PRETEXT:Assigned by DM							DESC:Thanks to the favor of the goddess of freedom, you are difficult to restrain.																																																									BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|2|TYPE=Sacred							COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:You gain a +2 sacred bonus on Escape Artist checks and a +2 sacred bonus on saving throws against any effect that would cause you to become paralyzed, held, or entangled. If you fail a saving t hrow a gainst s uch an e ffect, y ou c an a ttempt a s econd saving throw 1 round later. If you succeed on the second saving throw, you are affected as though you had succeeded on the first.
Spider Bite				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Vile		PREALIGN:LE,NE,CE					PREDEITY:1,Lolth	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Verminfriend											PRETEXT:Assigned by DM	SAB:1d4 STR damage/1d4 STR damage	DESC:You gain a poisonous bite like that of a spider.																																																																					BONUS:VAR|PoisonDC|(TL/2)-(HD/2)	COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:Your saliva is poisonous when ingested by or introduced into the bloodstream of another creature. You can inject this venom while grappling a foe that has exposed skin by making a successful grapple check. The Fortitude DC to resist this poison is 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Con modifier. The initial and secondary damage ratings are the same (1d4 points of Strength damage). Your kiss is also poisonous, and you can use your saliva to poison food or drink, though when the poison is ingested, the save DC is reduced by 2.
Touch of Hate			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Vile		PREALIGN:LE,NE,CE					PREDEITY:1,Bane	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Violate Spell							PRESPELLTYPE:1,Divine=5	PRETEXT:Assigned by DM							DESC:Because you are favored by Bane, you can transform animals into evil minions.																																																																						COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:Once per tenday, you can touch an animal and transform it into a beast of Bane (same as the Beast of Xvim entry in Monster Compendium: Monsters of Faerun). The animal can have no more Hit Dice prior to transformation than you have cleric levels. The target creature can resist the transformation by making a successful Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 your cleric level + your Wis modifier). If the animal is the bonded companion of another character, it can use that character's base Will save bonus instead of its own, applying its own ability modifiers. If it fails the save, it instantaneously transforms into a beast of Bane and follows your commands. The beast of Bane that you create deals vile damage with its smite good a bility. Vile damage can be healed only by magic cast within the area of a consecrate or hallow spell.

